HEADWORD: Lanarkite
<hw>Lan"ark*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Lanark</etsep>shire, a county in Scotland.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral consisting of sulphate of lead,
occurring either massive or in long slender prisms, of a greenish white
or gray color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lanary</ent>⟦br⟧
